formatted_items.content:
Below is a concise set of points you can forward to MedTech. I focused on data-privacy safeguards, day-to-day usability for our clinicians, and overall workflow alignment with the clinic.

Patient Profile Management – Harmony Health Clinic Feedback
-----------------------------------------------------------
Data privacy & security
• Current role-based access is solid, but we need field-level restrictions for sensitive developmental/psych notes.  
• Add automatic session-timeout (≤15 min inactivity) – our exam rooms are shared.  
• Audit-trail exports are helpful; would like an on-screen “last viewed / last edited by” banner for quick verification.  
• Confirm that PHI in exports is encrypted at rest on MedTech’s servers; wording in the SLA is a bit ambiguous.

Usability & interface
• Patient header is clear, but key autism-specific flags (sensory sensitivities, communication preferences) are two clicks deep—suggest surfacing as badges in the header.  
• Intake form auto-save is appreciated; however, keyboard navigation is inconsistent in the “Goals & Progress” section (tab order skips drop-downs).  
• Clinicians would benefit from customizable “quick notes” templates; current free-text field leads to wide variation.

Workflow fit
• Overall flow mirrors our current paper charting, minimizing training time.  
• Timeline view is excellent for multidisciplinary teams; consider color-coding by discipline (OT, SLP, psychology).  
• We need a lightweight way to record group-session attendance without duplicating entries in every child’s profile.  
• Discharge workflow lacks a prompt for final parent-feedback survey, which is a quality-metric requirement for us.

Miscellaneous
• Mobile app is stable but still read-only; adding note entry (even voice-to-text) would help therapists during home visits.  
• Please share ETA for HL7/FHIR integration with our EHR (Harmony uses CareConnect v5.4) so we can plan data migration.

Let me know if you need anything expanded or re-phrased.
